To run in Fast Restart mode again, use data with dimensions that match those of the From Workspace output signal. Otherwise, exit Fast Restart mode and start a new simulation.

Read data values specified in timeseries, matrix, or structure format from the MATLAB workspace, model workspace, or mask workspace.

MATLAB timeseries format may be used for any data type, complexity, or fixed dimensions. To load data for a bus signal, use a MATLAB structure that matches the bus hierarchy and specify timeseries for each leaf signal.

For matrix formats, each row of the matrix has a time stamp in the first column and a vector containing the corresponding data sample in the subsequent column(s).

For structure format, use the following kind of structure:
 var.time=[TimeValues]
 var.signals.values=[DataValues]
 var.signals.dimensions=[DimValues]

Input format not supported. Available formats include: (1) a Simulink.SimulationData.Dataset object, (2) a double non-complex matrix, (3) a structure with or without time, (4) a MATLAB timeseries object, (5) a structure with MATLAB timeseries objects at all leaves (for bus input). All formats require the data to be finite (not Inf or NaN).

A non-scalar Simulink.SimulationData.Dataset object used for external input. When using a Simulink.SimulationData.Dataset object for external input, even though it may contain multiple elements, the object itself must be a scalar.

Input format not supported. Available formats include: (1) a Simulink.SimulationData.Dataset object, (2) a Simulink.SimulationData.DatasetRef object, (3) a double non-complex matrix, (4) a structure with or without time, (5) a MATLAB timeseries object, (6) a structure with MATLAB timeseries objects at all leaves (for bus input). All formats require the data to be finite (not Inf or NaN).

A non-scalar Simulink.SimulationData.DatasetRef object used for external input. When using a Simulink.SimulationData.DatasetRef object for external input, even though it may reference a Dataset with multiple elements, the object itself must be a scalar.
Model input cannot combine Simulink.Timeseries or Simulink.TsArray formats with MATLAB timeseries formats (including structure of MATLAB timeseries).

For this timeseries, the combination of the IsTimeFirst property and the dimensionality of the Data property is not supported. To load data for this input, update the dimension of the Data property of the timeseries object:\n -If the signal is a scalar or a 1-D vector, time must be the first dimension.\n -If the signal has more than 1 dimension, time must be the last dimension.

Invalid Simulink.Timeseries variable specified as {0} input in ''{1}''. The Data property must be a built-in numeric, logical, fixed point or enumerated type. The dimensions of the Data property must be non-zero.

Matrix input can only be used if all the signals connected to the root inports are real (non-complex), double vectors.

Invalid workspace data format for root Inport ''{0}''. The model is configured to load its root level ports from the workspace. This root Inport is configured to output a function call. Use one of these approaches: a) For the workspace data to be loaded, use a column vector of monotonically non-decreasing time values; b) For this root Inport, clear the ''Output function call'' block parameter; or c) Turn off loading of external inputs by clearing the Configuration Parameters -> Data Import/Export -> Input parameter.

Invalid workspace data format for root Inport ''{0}''. The model is configured to load its root level ports from the workspace. The workspace data specified for this root Inport is a column vector; you should use that format only with a root Inport that outputs a function-call signal. Use one of these approaches: a) For the workspace data to be loaded, use a format other than a column vector; b) For this root Inport, select the ''Output function call'' block parameter; or c) Turn off loading of external inputs by clearing the Configuration Parameters -> Data Import/Export -> Input parameter.

To load external data of non-double data type, change the external input to use structure format, timeseries format, or disable loading of external input. Loading of external inputs is disabled by going to the Simulation menu and selecting Configuration Parameters. On the Data Import/Export page, locate the Load from workspace group and uncheck the Input checkbox.

To construct a MATLAB structure from a bus object, the first argument must be the name of a bus object. However, the names of the fields in the structure of timeseries can be different from the nodes defined in the bus object.
